s instead of direct mutation.\\n- `addPostLockCommit(planId, commitData, reason)`: creates commit + scope change event (COMMIT_ADDED).\\n- `removePostLockCommit(commitId, reason)`: marks commit canceled + scope change event (COMMIT_REMOVED).\\n- `editPostLockCommit(commitId, changes, reason)`: applies changes + scope change event per changed field (ESTIMATE_CHANGED, CHESS_PIECE_CHANGED, RCDO_CHANGED, PRIORITY_CHANGED). Each event stores before/after values.\\n- Reason text required for all material changes.\\n- `getChangeTimeline(planId)`: returns chronological scope change events.\\n- Manager exception detection: flag if change crosses threshold (e.g., King added/changed, total points increased >20%, etc.).\\n\\n**ReconciliationService:**\\n- Automatic LOCKED → RECONCILING transition at configured reconcile-open time (background job, idempotent).\\n- `getReconciliationView(planId)`: returns baseline snapshot commits alongside current commit values, scope change summary, and linked ticket current statuses.\\n- `setCommitOutcome(commitId, outcome, notes)`: sets outcome (ACHIEVED, PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED, NOT_ACHIEVED, CANCELED). Notes required for PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED, NOT_ACHIEVED, and CANCELED.\\n- Auto-achieve: if a linked ticket has status DONE at reconciliation time, auto-set outcome to ACHIEVED.\\n- `submitReconciliation(planId)`: validates all commits have outcomes. Creates ReconcileSnapshotHeader + ReconcileSnapshotCommit rows (normalized + denormalized JSON). Transitions RECONCILING → RECONCILED. Sets compliance flags.\\n\\n**REST endpoints:**\\n- `POST /api/plans/{id}/scope-changes` — add/remove/edit post-lock\\n- `GET /api/plans/{id}/scope-changes` — change timeline\\n- `GET /api/plans/{id}/reconcile` — reconciliation view\\n- `PUT /api/plans/{id}/commits/{commitId}/outcome` — set outcome\\n- `POST /api/plans/{id}/reconcile/submit` — submit reconciliation\\n\\n**Unit tests:** scope change event creation with before/after, reason validation, auto-achieve from Done